Joralemon Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Clinton Street, showing at the corner, No. 153, the home of Dr. G. Johnson. Upon this site now (1929) stands the Clinton Arms, a 6-story structure.
About 1890.

The 10-story building at the left, belongs to the B.M.T Corp. Also seen at the left, is the Spence Memorial Presbyterian Church.
